args: I know, sweetheart... Mama is so sorry\nshe can't get you anything to eat!
This town is suffering from terrible famine.\nI feel awful for them.
Indeed. Evidently, their harvest was a\npoor one.
Well, I'd like to do something to help.\nSurely we can spare some food?
We could, but some would still go hungry.\nWe don't have enough on hand.
Then we'll just have to make a few trips.\nBut that will take some time...

Never fear, for Jiang Ziya is here!
When rumblin' stomachs abound,
there's a relic to make 'em round!
...Like, because they're full of food.
You just put a drop of it on something,\nand then suddenly that thing is doubled!
You mean if you had one loaf of bread\nit would become two, then four,\nthen eight, and so forth?
My word... With a relic like that, we could\nutterly transform the Halidom's finances...
Why did you not tell us of it sooner?!
What?! Wh-why are you mad at me?!
I'm not mad—I'm delighted! Incredibly so!
You are? Hmm, you're a tricky one to\nread, Cleo.
Ha ha... Well, in any case, please do use\nyour relic to multiply our food supply!
Aye-aye, captain! Let's go ahead and just\nput a drop on this here bread...

O power universal of the Qilin, be bound
by my solemn decree. Replicator Dew.
Inexhaustible immensity. Strong and
swift may you invoke your gift!
With this, I may finally escape the\nshackles of food expenses...
Um, Cleo? You still with us?\nYeah, no. She's gone.
Then let's you and I take this bread to\nthe townsfolk!
I can really have this bread?!
Of course! Eat as much as you like!
Thank you so very much! How can I ever\nrepay you?
Please! Let me have some bread, too!
It's all right, no need to rush. We've got\nplenty more where this came from.
Really?! Oh, thank goodness!\nStarvation won't take us after all!
I'm sooo full. It's been a long time since I\nate this much.
Hee hee! Another good deed done!\nClassic me—genius all the way!
Yeah, but the bread sure did multiply\nfast. They ate a ton of it, but there's\nstill a mountain left over.
It's exponential growth, after all.\nA hundred becomes two hundred\nbecomes four hundred, and so forth
When you stop to consider it, that sort\nof multiplicative increase is actually\nrather frightening.
For sure. If the bread kept producing\nat that rate, it would practically flood\nthe village.
Yes, but never mind the village—before\nlong, the entire continent would be buried\nunder an ocean of bread loaves.
That should be the yeast of your worries!\nAll's I need to do is stop the relic's effect\nbefore any untimely bread-burying.

O power universal of the Qilin, be bound
by my solemn decree. Replicator Dew.
Inexhaustible immensity. Be your
exertions henceforth suppressed!
That's a relief. Everything should be\nfine now.
Uh, wait... Why is the bread still\nmultiplying?
AAACK! Oh, that's right! I forgot!
You can't just stop this relic's effect all\nat once—you have to cancel the effect\non every loaf individually!
Yeah! O power universal of the Qilin,\nbe bound by my solemn decree!\nO power universal of the—
Ack! Please, hurry! They're multiplying\nfaster than we're stopping them!
Th-this is bad! At this rate, the world's\ngonna be destroyed in a flood of bread!
No! I shall not allow it!

O power universal of the Qilin,
be bound by my solemn decree.
Eternal coffin, the way boundless! Shatter
all boundaries and reveal infinity itself!
The bread is being swallowed up by a\ntear into the otherworld!
...I used the Hong Hulu. If the bread is\nsent to the space between worlds, then\nit cannot wreak havoc here.
Xuan Zang! I knew it was you!
Yes. I sensed Qilin relics in use, and made\nmy way here with haste. I can scarcely\nbelieve the scene that awaited me.
I shudder to think what could have\nhappened had I been any later.
Hey, thanks a million! You've got some\npretty amazing Qilin relics on you!
You are Qilin... Then it was you, yes?\nYou used the relic.
Yup. I used the Replicator Dew on the\nbread to multiply it.
Everyone here was starving. I just wanted\nto do what I could to help them.
You used a Qilin relic to...help people?
What's with the surprise?\nI'm a genius, duh!
That is a quite a bold claim.
In any case, I have a number of things\nI'd like to ask you, but we shall first\nhelp the people here.

We're truly sorry for the trouble! You have
my word that any who still require food or
have lost their homes will be welcomed
with open arms at the Halidom!
...I see. You wish to enable others to live\nlives of ease and comfort by making\ncommon the use of Qilin relics.
She can't bear to stand by and watch\npeople suffer. I can understand that.
After all, I, too, broke the Sealer code\nto concern myself with the world at large.
Then you and I are like two peas in a pod,\nXuan Zang!
I may have broken the Sealer code,\nbut I have no intention of breaking\nthe code of the Qilin tribe as well.

However noble your reasons, spreading
Qilin relics around the world so lightly
is something I have serious reservations
about.
Thus, I shall accompany you for the time\nbeing, so that I may determine the merits\nof your conduct!
